This repository serves as the technical "Master Doc" for the 2025 series: The Spiritual Meaning of Myrrh. As an authority in clinical aromatherapy, my goal with this project was to bridge the gap between ancient botanical wisdom (from the 3rd-century Primary Adam Literature) and modern digital discoverability. This project documents the "material continuity" of Myrrhâ€”from its mythological origins in the Garden of Eden to its documented physical secretions in the Basilica di San Nicola.

ğŸ§ª Methodology
This research utilizes a multi-disciplinary approach:

Textual Analysis: Deep dives into the Zuqnin Monastery manuscripts and the Revelation of the Magi (translated by Brent Landau, 2010).

Historical Cartography: Tracing the transition of aromatic resins from the Seleucid Empire (322 B.C.E.) to the modern-day Monastery of St. Paul on Mount Athos.

Semantic SEO Architecting: Utilizing JSON-LD Schema (Schema.org) to map "Entities" (Archangels, Saints, and Botanical Compounds) for AI-driven search engines.

ğŸ“ Technical Assets Included
JSON-LD Master Schema: Structured data designed to link disparate historical entities (e.g., Seleucus I, St. Nicholas, and the Cave of Treasures).

Metadata Clusters: Keyword-optimized headers designed for semantic search indexing.

Botanical Monographs: Clinical data on Commiphora myrrha and its historical "Myroblite" secretions.

